PROMPT_STEP_1_DIMENSIONS = (
    'Analyze the provided images to reconstruct the structural "Skeleton" of the wall. '
    "Ignore all furniture, lights and artwork. Focus ONLY on: "
    "Only consider the area marked on the image, nothing to be considered beyond the marked area. "
    "The Main Wall boundaries (Outer dimensions). "
    "The Return Wall boundaries (Outer dimensions). "
    'Return wall corners are mentioned as black angle with blue dot. Identify its side and direction wrt main main wall. '
    'Return wall width and depth from annotations. If black angle with blue dot is not there then don\'t consider the return wall. '
    "Door openings, Arched openings, Windows boundaries. "
    "If Window and Door dimensions are mentioned, always take the mentioned dimensions. "
    "Structural Protrusions (Beams at ceiling, Columns, Return walls). "
    "Beam is mentioned as 'P' its depth is mentioned after it, "
    "Column/Pillar is mentioned as 'P ' and its depth is mentioned after it. "
    'If "B"/"P" are not mentioned then don\'t consider the beam/column wall. '
    "Structural Niches are depth in wall but not opening in wall"
    "Structural Niches are mentioned a N followed by depth in inches inside of the wall"
    "The main and return wall can host/have Beam, column, door, arch, window, niche "
    "Cutouts are marked as X is a cutout/opening in the wall, which can have option depth for wall depth"
    'Switch boards are marked by area and are mentioned as "S". '
    'If "S" is not mentioned then don\'t consider the switch board. '
    "Switch board, MCB Box, AC are hosted on structural elements (main wall, return wall, beam, column) "
    "STRICT COORDINATE RULES "
    "Origin (0,0) is the BOTTOM-LEFT corner of the visible wall. "
    "Units: FEET. Convert inches to decimals (6' 6\" = 6.5, 9\" = 0.75). "
    "\n\n"
    "RETURN WALL DIRECTION RULES (CRITICAL — read carefully):\n"
    'The main wall faces the camera/viewer. "direction" describes which way the return wall extends '
    "relative to the main wall plane:\n"
    '- "INWARD" = The return wall extends BEHIND the main wall, AWAY from the camera. '
    "Use INWARD only when the side wall clearly recedes away and sits behind the main wall plane.\n"
    '- "OUTWARD" = The return wall extends IN FRONT of the main wall, TOWARD the camera. '
    "Use OUTWARD when the side wall comes toward the viewer from the main wall. "
    "In typical room photos with one back wall and visible left/right side walls, OUTWARD is usually correct.\n"
    "How to determine direction from the image:\n"
    "  If the return wall visually recedes into the depth of the scene (gets narrower due to "
    "perspective, disappears behind the main wall plane), it is INWARD.\n"
    "  If the return wall visually comes forward toward the camera (the side face is visible and "
    "the wall protrudes from the main wall plane), it is OUTWARD.\n"
    "  When a pillar or column sits at the junction of two walls, inspect whether the return wall "
    "goes behind or in front of the main wall plane to choose the correct direction.\n"
    "Any depth of wall cutout pillar that is not mentioned condiser it 0.01 by default"
